            <p>
                According to data pooled by the UNESCO Institute for Statistics (UIS)’s Women In Science interactive  tool, only less than 30% of women are researchers in the field of science globally. While it is difficult to quantify the percentage of women in STEM field globally due to a variety of reasons, such as the difference in the definition of terminologies across countries etc, the UIS is developing new indicators to better understand the dynamics that shape women’s decisions to seek a career in STEM-related fields, showing the extent to which family decisions, financial considerations, workplace culture and discrimination can shape women’s career choices and progression in these areas.
            </p>
            <p>Hence the reason for this form/survey. This survey aims to collect data about women in Tech who may not have been involved in the last survey.</p>
